@startuml seq-propagation
title Propagation v1.0.0+ - hash on the wire + Redis fallback + bootstrap-then-auth (v1.2.0 fromDbSeed, v1.3.0 purpose)

skinparam sequenceMessageAlign center
skinparam shadowing false

actor "Source app\n(boot / syncFromConfig)" as App
participant "propagateClientToApis\n(http/init)" as Propagate
database "Redis (source)" as RedisSrc
participant "createHttpSignedFetchClient\n(signer)" as Signer
participant "hashClientSecret\n(core/crypto)" as Hash
collections "Target API\n/api/internal/hmac" as Target
participant "handleInternalManagementRequest\n(http/init)" as Handler
participant "verifyHttpSignature" as Verify
database "Redis (target)" as RedisTgt

== Source: resolve the secretHash to ship ==
App -> Propagate : propagateClientToApis({\n  operation: "create",\n  clientId, secret? / secretHash?,\n  allowedIps, targets, apiFetch\n})
alt secretHash explicit (priority 1)
  Propagate -> Propagate : resolvedSecretHash = secretHash
else secret + secretHash both omitted (priority 2)
  Propagate -> RedisSrc : credentialStore.getClientRecord(clientId)
  alt local record found
    RedisSrc --> Propagate : {secretHash_local, ...}
    Propagate -> Propagate : resolvedSecretHash = secretHash_local
  else not found
    RedisSrc --> Propagate : null
    Propagate -> App : throw "secret or secretHash is required\n(or clientId must exist locally)"
  end
else secret plain provided (priority 3)
  Propagate -> Hash : hashClientSecret(secret, localSecretToken)
  Hash --> Propagate : secretHash (local hash)
end
note right of Propagate
  payload.secretHash is set
  payload.secret is NEVER sent
end note

== Source: sign the propagation request itself ==
App -> Signer : pre-built signer (clientId = signerClientId,\nsecret = signerCredential.secretHash, secretIsHashed: true)
note over Signer
  Signing key for THE PROPAGATION CALL
  is the local secretHash of the signer
  (e.g. self_propagation_signer).
end note

== Target receives the POST ==
Propagate -> Target : POST <target>/api/internal/hmac\nHeaders: x-client-id, x-timestamp, x-nonce, x-signature\nBody: {clientId, secretHash, allowedIps, fromDbSeed?, purpose?, ...}\n(fromDbSeed only emitted when true; v1.2.0)\n(purpose only emitted when set; v1.3.0)
Target -> Handler : handleInternalManagementRequest(input)
Handler -> RedisTgt : clients.listClientIds()
RedisTgt --> Handler : knownClients
alt knownClients.length == 0  (bootstrap mode)
  note over Handler
    First propagated client lands here.
    No HMAC verification - the route
    is "bootstrap-then-auth".

    v1.3.0: when requireBootstrapClientId is
    configured, the bootstrap POST is accepted
    only when payload.clientId equals the
    named clientId. Other clientIds -> 403
    BOOTSTRAP_LOCKED (see seq-bootstrap-lock).
  end note
else knownClients.length > 0  (auth required)
  Handler -> Verify : verifyHttpSignature(...)
  Verify -> RedisTgt : credentialStore.getClientRecord(callerClientId)
  RedisTgt --> Verify : record or null
  alt signer unknown / hash mismatch / IP filter
    Verify -> Handler : throw HmacAuthError
    Handler -> Target : 403 "Internal HMAC management\nauthentication failed"
    Target --> Propagate : 403 result\nresult.accepted = false
  end
  note over Verify
    v1.3.0: the propagation signer is typically
    declared with purpose="propagation-only".
    The signed request targets the management
    route -> cantonment check passes. Any signed
    request on a business path would throw
    PROPAGATION_ONLY_FORBIDDEN (403) here
    (see seq-purpose-cantonment).
  end note
end

Handler -> RedisTgt : clients.get(payload.clientId)
alt clientId already exists
  RedisTgt --> Handler : record
  Handler -> Target : 403 "Client already exists"
  Target --> Propagate : 403 result\n(treat as success when retrying)
else not yet present
  RedisTgt --> Handler : null
  Handler -> RedisTgt : clients.setSecretHash(clientId, payload.secretHash,\nexpiresAt, allowedIps, { fromDbSeed?, purpose? })
  note right of RedisTgt
    Hash stored AS-IS.
    No re-hash with the target's
    HMAC_SECRET_TOKEN.
    Source and target Redis now
    hold byte-identical hashes.

    v1.3.0: when payload.purpose is set
    ("propagation-only"), the value is
    persisted on the record and enforced
    by verifyHttpSignature on every
    subsequent signed call.
  end note
  RedisTgt --> Handler : stored
  Handler -> Target : 201 "create accepted"
  Target --> Propagate : 201 result\nresult.accepted = true
end

Propagate --> App : results[] {target, url, status, accepted, body, error?}

== Downstream effect: signed requests now work cross-token ==
note over RedisSrc, RedisTgt
  Subsequent signed HTTP calls from source to target succeed:
  both verifyHttpSignature compute HMAC(secretHash, payload)
  with the same secretHash, even if source and target
  do NOT share the same HMAC_SECRET_TOKEN.
end note

@enduml
